---
description: Enforce gameplay/doc sync on implementation changes
alwaysApply: true
---

When making gameplay, data model, or game-flow changes, documentation must be updated in the same task.

## Trigger
Apply this rule whenever changes touch:
- scripts/game_scene.gd
- scripts/game_state.gd
- scripts/play_resolver.gd
- scripts/card_manager.gd
- scripts/effect_manager.gd
- scripts/targeting_manager.gd
- scenes/game_scene.tscn
- scenes/field.tscn
- scripts/field_grid.gd
- scripts/field_grid_overlay.gd
- data/*.json

## Required doc sync
Update all relevant docs from this list based on what changed:
- docs/Gameplay_Summary.md
- docs/Properties.md
- docs/Team_Setup.md
- docs/Screens.md
- docs/Todo List.md
- docs/Abbreviations.md
- docs/Ideas.md
- docs/Implementation_Plan.md
- docs/Worldbuilding.md
- docs/Systems.md
- docs/Data_Architecture.md
- docs/Player_Generation.md
- docs/Balancing.md
- docs/Progression.md
- docs/Art_Direction.md

## Mapping guardrail (minimum expectations)
- Game flow/phases/conversions/clock/turnovers/downs -> docs/Gameplay_Summary.md + Implementation_Plan.md
- Stats/properties/schema/field names -> docs/Properties.md + Implementation_Plan.md + Balancing.md
- Species/archetypes/traits/synergies/generation -> docs/Systems.md + Data_Architecture.md + Player_Generation.md + Properties.md
- Training/recruitment/monetization -> docs/Progression.md + Gameplay_Summary.md
- Lore/setting/tone -> docs/Worldbuilding.md + Gameplay_Summary.md
- Art/visual readability -> docs/Art_Direction.md + Screens.md
- Team roles, formations, lineups, setup rules -> docs/Team_Setup.md + Implementation_Plan.md
- UI/HUD/screen behavior -> docs/Screens.md + Implementation_Plan.md
- New work items / follow-ups -> docs/Todo List.md
- New terms/acronyms -> docs/Abbreviations.md
- Design notes/parking-lot decisions -> docs/Ideas.md

## Conflict handling
If docs and code differ:
1) Call out the conflict explicitly.
2) Propose smallest alignment update.
3) Update docs to match implemented behavior unless user asks otherwise.

## Scope discipline
- Do not rewrite entire docs.
- Edit only impacted sections.
- Keep wording concise and implementation-accurate.

## Completion checklist (must satisfy before done)
- [ ] Relevant docs updated
- [ ] Implementation_Plan.md updated when behavior/scope changed
- [ ] Any code-doc conflicts called out and resolved
- [ ] Summary includes which docs were updated
